init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can't be sure if you're going to die of cancer or old age.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You smile, and she smiles back.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You both know that you've lived a good life.
